                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d734">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/504a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-12-27T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 27, 1924—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>317. Department’s No. 308, December 9, 4 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d734fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1924v01#pg_580">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1924, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 580</ref>.</note> Colonel Manton Davis,
                    Assistant General Attorney, Radio Corporation, will sail for China at an early
                    date to assist Barnes Moss in negotiations. It is; understood Moss has sailed,
                    or is about to sail, for China.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
